  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_4' aria-label=\" M/s Motilal Agarwala versus State of West Bengal & Anr. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('4','2025','2025_8_2400_2415','2025INSC1062'); ><font size='4'> <strong>M/S MOTILAL AGARWALA<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>STATE OF WEST BENGAL & ANR. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 8 S.C.R. 2400</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 1062</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010008582025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : J.B. PARDIWALA, K.V. VISWANATHAN</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Issue arose whether the delivery of the true/xerox copy of the Arbitral Award duly signed by the Arbitrator to an authorised representative of the State would constitute delivery upon the respondent in accordance with s.31(5) of the 1996 Act. Headnotes&dagger; Arbitration &ndash; ss.31(5), 2(1) (h) &ndash; Form and contents of arbitral award &ndash; Delivery of signed copy to each party &ndash; Delivery of the true/xerox copy of the Arbitral Award duly signed by the Arbitrator to Assistant Engineer-authorised representative of the State on 12.11.2013 &ndash;<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 28-08-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 4480/2016</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Dismissed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('4','2025','2025_8_2400_2415','2025INSC1062','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('4','2025','